netmask.sh - A BASH script to determine the range of IP address of a nework.

Read the network address in the form of:
192.268.1.0/24

Usage:

1. Run netmask
and then enter the <IP/netmask>

e.g.:
chris@acer:~/Documents/notes/scripts/netmask$ ./netmask.sh 
Enter the IP address: 192.168.1.100/24
Lowest IP: 192.168.1.0
Highest IP: 192.168.1.255

OR

2. netmask.sh <IP/netmask>
e.g.:
./netmask.sh 192.168.1.100/24 
Lowest IP: 192.168.1.0
Highest IP: 192.168.1.255
